comments.body:
@TomSweeneyRedHat @lsm5 PTAL.  I chatted with David Shea, and he and I both agree we shouldn't make perfection the enemy of good enough.

These fixes are very overdue, and we have a pile of issues following right behind.  Meaning it's probably not worth spending additional weeks/month fixing up the ginkgo tests for likely only a marginal gain (and keeping all the other issues on hold).  There will be plenty of additional opportunities to address any bugs or shortcomings in future PRs.

Unless someone has a quick way to get some ballpark :+1: / :-1: feedback, I'd be open to that.  I just don't have the willpower to shove this boulder up the rest of the mountain, nor do I think it necessary.

LGTM
@cevich we need to get WIP off of the title if you think it's good to go.
@lsm5 @dashea or @containers/podman-maintainers we need another review or three here.  Yeah, it's a beast.  681K lines of change, ouch!

FWIW, I asked Gemini to review it too, it was happy with it other than the WIP title.
